{"status":{"code":200,"http":"Fetched (ping) 200 2684 and parsed 1/9 entries","nextFetch":1505295,"entriesCountSinceLastMaintenance":1,"velocity":0.7,"popularity":4.022478890784052,"generatedIds":true,"period":2684,"lastFetch":1505293,"lastParse":1505293,"lastMaintenanceAt":1505229,"feed":"http://feeds.feedburner.com/symfony/blog"},"permalinkUrl":"http://symfony.com/blog/","standardLinks":{"alternate":[{"title":"Symfony Blog","rel":"alternate","href":"http://symfony.com/blog/","type":"text/html"}],"self":[{"title":"Symfony Blog","rel":"self","href":"http://feeds.feedburner.com/symfony/blog","type":"application/rss+xml"}],"hub":[{"title":"","rel":"hub","href":"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/","type":"text/html"}]},"title":"Symfony Blog","updated":1505292360,"id":"symfony-blog-2017-9-13-9","items":[{"id":"http://symfony.com/blog/new-in-symfony-3-4-user-impersonation-improvements","published":1505292360,"updated":1505292360,"title":"New in Symfony 3.4: User impersonation improvements","summary":"<p><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://symfony.com/doc/current/security/impersonating_user.html\">User impersonation</a> is a popular Symfony security feature that allows you to\nbrowse the application as if you were another user, for instance when you are\ndebugging or trying to understand a bug a user sees that you can't reproduce.\nIn Symfony 3.4 we improved this feature a bit to make it easier to debug.</p>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"added-the-impersonator-to-the-log-context\">\n<h1>Added the impersonator to the log context<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#added-the-impersonator-to-the-log-context\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">¶</a></h1>\n<div style=\"border-radius: 4px; float: right; margin-left: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; width: 200px; background-color: #fff7c4; padding: 7px\">\n    <div style=\"float: left; padding-top: 3px; width: 50px;\">\n        <a href=\"https://connect.sensiolabs.com/profile/gharlan\">\n            <img style=\"border-radius: 40px;\" height=\"40\" width=\"40\" src=\"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/330436\" alt=\"Gregor Harlan\">\n        </a>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"float: left;\">\n        <p style=\"font-size: 80%; margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0\">\n            Contributed by <br>\n            <a href=\"https://connect.sensiolabs.com/profile/gharlan\">Gregor Harlan </a> <br>\n            in <a href=\"https://github.com/symfony/symfony/pull/24026\">#24026</a>.\n        </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"clear_fix\"></div>\n</div><p>The well known security log message <em>&quot;User was reloaded from a user provider.&quot;</em>\nincludes the user provider and the username of the impersonated user in its\ncontext. In Symfony 3.4, to make things easier to debug, this context will also\ninclude the username of the impersonator user via the <code class=\"notranslate\">impersonator_username</code>\nkey.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"section\" id=\"added-impersonation-details-in-the-debug-toolbar\">\n<h1>Added impersonation details in the debug toolbar<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#added-impersonation-details-in-the-debug-toolbar\" title=\"Permalink to this headline\">¶</a></h1>\n<div style=\"border-radius: 4px; float: right; margin-left: 15px; margin-bottom: 15px; width: 200px; background-color: #fff7c4; padding: 7px\">\n    <div style=\"float: left; padding-top: 3px; width: 50px;\">\n        <a href=\"https://connect.sensiolabs.com/profile/yonelceruto\">\n            <img style=\"border-radius: 40px;\" height=\"40\" width=\"40\" src=\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4ba9f5f004ad32e2a74ec4690212de11?s=100\" alt=\"Yonel Ceruto \">\n        </a>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"float: left;\">\n        <p style=\"font-size: 80%; margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0\">\n            Contributed by <br>\n            <a href=\"https://connect.sensiolabs.com/profile/yonelceruto\">Yonel Ceruto </a> <br>\n            in <a href=\"https://github.com/symfony/symfony/pull/23026\">#23026</a>.\n        </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"clear_fix\"></div>\n</div><p>In Symfony 3.4, the security panel of the Web Debug Toolbar will include more\ndetails when using impersonation. First, it will also show the username of the\nimpersonator user. Second, it will include a link to exit from the impersonation:</p>\n<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/60369767@N00/36364456964\"><img class=\"screenshot\" src=\"https://farm5.staticflickr.com/4359/36364456964_c0b8237a47_o.png\"></a></div>\n\n                <hr style=\"margin-bottom: 5px\" />\n                <div style=\"font-size: 90%\">\n                Be trained by <a href=\"https://training.sensiolabs.com/en/courses?q=symfony\">Symfony experts</a>\n                                - <a href=\"http://training.sensiolabs.com/en/courses?q=SF3C2&amp;from=09/13/2017&amp;to=09/14/2017\">2017-09-13</a> Paris\n                                - <a href=\"http://training.sensiolabs.com/en/courses?q=SF3C3&amp;from=09/18/2017&amp;to=09/19/2017\">2017-09-18</a> Paris\n                                - <a href=\"http://training.sensiolabs.com/en/courses?q=SF3C1&amp;from=09/25/2017&amp;to=09/26/2017\">2017-09-25</a> Cologne\n                                </div><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/symfony/blog/~4/Lkvd280KxFE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>","permalinkUrl":"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/symfony/blog/~3/Lkvd280KxFE/new-in-symfony-3-4-user-impersonation-improvements","standardLinks":{"alternate":[{"title":"New in Symfony 3.4: User impersonation improvements","rel":"alternate","href":"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/symfony/blog/~3/Lkvd280KxFE/new-in-symfony-3-4-user-impersonation-improvements","type":"text/html"}],"replies":[{"title":"New in Symfony 3.4: User impersonation improvements","rel":"replies","href":"http://symfony.com/blog/new-in-symfony-3-4-user-impersonation-improvements#comments-list","type":"text/html"}],"canonical":[{"title":"New in Symfony 3.4: User impersonation improvements","rel":"canonical","href":"http://symfony.com/blog/new-in-symfony-3-4-user-impersonation-improvements","type":"text/html"}]},"actor":{"displayName":"Javier Eguiluz","id":"Javier Eguiluz"},"language":"en"}]}